<div class="question-card" id="card-13" data-qid="13" data-type="multi" data-choose="2">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 14</span>
    <span class="q-tag multi">Choose 2</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      Which two functions are performed at the MAC sublayer of the OSI Data Link Layer to facilitate Ethernet communication? (Choose two.)
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-13">
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">applies delimiting of Ethernet frame fields to synchronize communication between nodes</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">applies source and destination MAC addresses to Ethernet frame</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">places information in the Ethernet frame that identifies which network layer protocol is being encapsulated by the frame</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">handles communication between upper layer networking software and Ethernet NIC hardware</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn multi" data-idx="4">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">E</span>
        <span class="opt-text">adds Ethernet control information to network protocol data</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn multi-pending" id="submit-13" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
      <span class="pending-count" id="pendingCount-13">0 / 2 selected</span>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-13">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-13"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        The two functions performed at the MAC sublayer of the OSI Data Link Layer to facilitate Ethernet communication are:
        <ul>
          <li><strong>applies delimiting of Ethernet frame fields to synchronize communication between nodes</strong></li>
          <li><strong>applies source and destination MAC addresses to Ethernet frame</strong></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pagination-controls">
      <button class="nav-btn" id="prev-13">Previous</button>
      <span class="page-indicator">14 / 14</span>
      <button class="nav-btn" id="next-13">Next</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
